OL,3,CWhy these elections are so important
OL,5,FSo the outcome could be the definitive
OL,6,Fend of Britain's 250 years of two
OL,7,Fparty politics. And because this
OL,8,Fdegree of fragmentation is so new, it
OL,9,Fbrings enormous uncertainties and
OL,10,Fdangers.
OL,12,FIt means, for example, that - under
OL,13,Four first-past-the-post electoral
OL,14,Fsystem - a party could win the votes
OL,15,Fof just one-in-six of us and yet have
OL,16,Fan absolute majority of MPs.
OL,18,FFor the majority to be subject to rule
OL,19,Fby the representatives of such a small
OL,20,Fminority would be a duck that does not
OL,21,Fquack democracy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
